                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <head>204. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in India</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d204fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 691.93/11-1962. Top Secret; <gloss target="#t_Niact1">Niact</gloss>;
                        Verbatim Text. Drafted in S by William E. Knepper and approved by Breisky
                            (<gloss target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-11-19T22:01:00-05:00">November 19, 1962, 22:01 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2167. Eyes Only for Ambassador. The following letter was delivered to the
                    President by the Indian Ambassador this evening, and is transmitted for your
                    information in the event that a copy has not been delivered to Embassy.
                    Department comments will follow in separate telegram.</p>
                <p>“New Delhi 19th November 1962.</p>
                <p>[This letter has not been declassified by the Indian Government. For a summary,
                    see <ref target="#d203">Document 203</ref>.]<note n="1" xml:id="d204fn1">Printed
                        from a copy that has no signature.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
